Class QualitativeValue

java.lang.Object
com.iunera.jsonldjava.schemaorg.metadatatypes.Thing
com.iunera.jsonldjava.schemaorg.metadatatypes.Intangible
com.iunera.jsonldjava.schemaorg.metadatatypes.Enumeration
com.iunera.jsonldjava.schemaorg.metadatatypes.QualitativeValue
Direct Known Subclasses:
DriveWheelConfigurationValue, SteeringPositionValue
public class QualitativeValue extends Enumeration
A predefined value for a product characteristic, e.g. the power cord plug type 'US' or the garment sizes 'S', 'M', 'L', and 'XL'.

Note: Publishers should be aware that applications designed to use specific schema.org properties (e.g. http://schema.org/width, http://schema.org/color, http://schema.org/gtin13, ...) will typically expect such data to be provided using those properties, rather than using the generic property/value mechanism.
